During a visit to Detroit, Vice President Kamala Harris expressed gratitude for Governor Whitmer's commitment to the people of Michigan and emphasized the importance of partnerships in implementing initiatives that benefit the state. She praised the union work and apprenticeship training model in Detroit as a successful example of investing in technology and innovation. Harris highlighted the significance of the CHIPS and Science Act in addressing supply chain issues and promoting American manufacturing. She thanked Michigan for creating new automotive jobs and providing training opportunities for individuals to develop essential skills. The Vice President also addressed the importance of young voters and their impact on issues such as the climate crisis, student loan debt, and gun safety laws. She encouraged young Americans to use their voices through voting.